At least six people have been killed and 50 others injured when a bus rear-ended a stationary truck on the N8, outside of Bloemfontein in the Free State.Paramedics found the bus and truck on the side of the road. The entire one side of the bus was ripped open in the collision.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said: &#8220;paramedics found several patients lying next to the bus while numerous others were found walking around the scene.&#8221;It was also found that six women had sustained fatal injuries and unfortunately, they were declared dead on the scene.Assessments showed that 50 other patients injuries ranged from minor to critical.Paramedics treated the patients and provided the critically injured with advanced life support interventions. Once treated, patients were transported to various hospitals in the area for further treatment.The cause of the collision is still unknown but local authorities were on the scene for further investigations.TNA Reporter